<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15377] Do not swallow exceptions thrown in replication</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15377</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;em&gt;IndexFetcher&lt;/em&gt; swallows Exceptions upon replication errors and does not log the stack trace properly. This led to some confusion when setting up a TLOG/PULL replica ensemble.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I created a very small Pull Request that logs stack traces properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
